annotationA: SAGA-associated factor 29kDa, isoform A; Methylated histone binding; histone acetyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: chromatin remodeling; histone acetylation
annotationB: Cannonball (Can) is a testis-specific TBP-associated factor (tTAF) essential for spermatogenesis. It is required for the normal level of expression of a large number of spermatogenesis genes. Can protein is strongly associated with the nucleolus in primary spermatocytes
